    "comment": "Rationale: Rab27b is present on a subset of synaptic vesicles where it is involved in the regulating of SV recycling.\n\nUniprot: has lipid anchor. Experimental description: Sequencing of cDNA encoded by plasmid. Not mentioned in the paper.\n\n19/01/2017 Pim\nNote: please note that the expert that created this annotation is part of the lab that created this publication. The species information is therefore derived from direct communication with the authors.\n\n3/2/2017 Pim:\nNote: the Rab27b protein is shown to be preset in rat preparations with antibodies (Fig.5). In Fig 7 Rab27b is shown to have functional consequens for SV release. For the CC anotation the rat data is sufficient; I corrected the species to Rat.",
